{
  "text": "For constraints (5)- (11), (5) [CITATION_1] can be rewritten in form of accumulation, i.e., [CITATION_2] . In (11), nn ij  means parking n i occurs no later than parking n j . And the middle part of each inequality in (11) represents the total recharged energy of PEB n during n j times parking. The first and last parts of each inequality in (11) respectively represent the lower and upper limits of total recharged energy of PEB n after n j times charging processes. Note that [CITATION_3] and (11) [CITATION_4] For constraints (19)-(24), [CITATION_5] and [CITATION_6] restrict the charging power and discharging power of ESS within the maximum powers, respectively; (21) describe the energy state transition of ESS; [CITATION_7] are the SOC range constraints for 6 ESS; (23) describe the mutual exclusion of charging and discharging states of ESS, i.e., avoid simultaneous charging and discharging of ESS; (24) is the energy balance constraint of ESS, since it is usually expected that the initial and final SOCs are same.",
